      • add

        public void add(com.google.gson.JsonObject root,
                T newValue)
         throws UnexpectedJsonElementTypeException
        Description copied from interface: JsonAccessor
        Add the given primitive value to the element this accessor points to for the given root.

        This method differs from JsonAccessor.set(JsonObject, Object):

        • If there is currently no value, the given value is simply set.
        • If the current value is an array, the given value is added to this array.
        • If the current value is a primitive or JsonNull, the current value is replaced by an array containing the current value followed by the given value.
        • Otherwise (i.e. if the current value is an object), an UnexpectedJsonElementTypeException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        root - The root to be accessed.
        newValue - The value to add.
        Throws:
        UnexpectedJsonElementTypeException - If an element in the path has unexpected type, preventing write access to the element this accessor points to.
